The provided documents describe the Polish Zloty as the currency of Poland, not the Grand Duchy of Lithuania.  File 88.txt mentions a "Czworak" coin from 1568 within the context of the Grand Duchy of Lithuania but doesn't specify it as the official currency.

mistral.reason: The Grand Duchy of Lithuania existed before the introduction of the modern Polish złoty, which was established in 1995. The coin presented (Czworak, 1568) predates the existence of the modern Polish złoty by more than three centuries.
